  "@id": "https://hydrography.org/#dataset",
  "name": "Hydrography90m",
  "url": "https://hydrography.org/",
  "description": "Hydrography90m is a high-resolution global hydrographic dataset derived from the MERIT Hydro digital elevation model at 3 arc-second (~90 m at the equator). It provides a globally seamless, standardized representation of stream channels and drainage basins with associated topographic and topological attributes for flow routing and network analysis. Products include stream and basin layers, sub-catchments linked to stream segments, stream order and slope metrics, flow-routing topology via unique segment identifiers, and tiled raster/vector layers suitable for large-scale hydrology, geomorphology, ecology, and environmental modeling applications.",
